2/19 (Sun) China‘spy balloon’wakes up world to new era of war at edge of space./ Do you have any tips to improve your memory? (Host: Ellen)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:35 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:35-9:00 pm Debate<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 1: China‘spy balloon’wakes up world to new era of war at edge of space.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/feb/10/china-spy-balloons-surveillance-high-altitude">https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/ ... h-altitude</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.What purposes do you think Chinese spy balloons for? <br /><br />2.Do you think the balloons can be the hostile force or a kind of weapons in the future? Are there any advantages for human beings?<br /><br />3.The advanced technology is around us, some of them just like the spy to monitor what you did (such like google engine, FB keyword, once you search it, it will pop up in your mobile phone automatically), how do you feel about it? How do you avoid this problem?<br /><br />4.Are you the person who enjoys learning new technology/ knowledge or against it? Please share your opinion.<br /><br /><br />------------------------------------------------------------<br />Session II: Do you have any tips to improve your memory?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lf5jOBEGGVw">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lf5jOBEGGVw</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.Do you agree with the author said “if you want to remember something, you want to adrenaline after”? Do you have any experience to share with us?<br /><br />2.Do you need concentrate/focus that you can improve your memory? Are you a person who can always be focused on things with any situations or noisy surroundings?<br /><br />3.Do you have any your own tips to improve your memory or work/study efficiency? Please share with us.<br /><br />4.Do you think take nap can improve your memory or work efficiently?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Tue Feb 14, 2023 11:34 am</p><hr />
